
(1). The way the researchers phrase their questions or options will influence participantsâ€™ choice of answer: for example, if the researcher phrased one choice in an unfavorable way, this might prompt participants to choose another answer.
 
(2). The influence of social desirability: the participants tend to choose answers that are socially
acceptable and some participants want to do good for the researchers.
 
(3). Participants might experience fatigue till the later half of the survey which might induce them to give more careless answers, or they can be careless throughout the whole survey.


